cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.CE, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the use of bots in online field experiments, which involves the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), as the paper focuses on the ethical challenges of using bots as virtual confederates in social science research. The paper also discusses the design space for bots, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the paper proposes guidelines for ethical experimentation, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
